# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — API Standards

---

## Response Envelope

All API responses MUST use this envelope format:

```json
{
  "data": { ... },
  "pagination": {
    "page": 1,
    "limit": 20,
    "total": 150,
    "totalPages": 8
  },
  "error": null
}
```

### Success (single item)
```json
{ "data": { "id": "...", ... }, "pagination": null, "error": null }
```

### Success (list)
```json
{ "data": [...], "pagination": { "page": 1, "limit": 20, "total": 42, "totalPages": 3 }, "error": null }
```

### Error
```json
{ "data": null, "pagination": null, "error": { "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR", "message": "...", "details": [...] } }
```

> **Frontend rule:** Always unwrap `response.data.data` — the API envelope wraps the actual payload.

